---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Refund Policy | Rustzen"
  description="Refund policy for Zen Clear Pro subscriptions purchased through Creem."
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal-document">
      <p class="eyebrow">Refund Policy</p>
      <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: June 25, 2026</p>

      <p>
        Zen Clear Pro is sold as an annual subscription through Creem. This
        policy explains how refund requests are handled.
      </p>

      <h2>Refund Window</h2>
      <p>
        You may request a refund within 14 days of the initial purchase or
        renewal if Zen Clear Pro does not work for you or you purchased by
        mistake. Refund requests should include the email used at checkout and
        the Creem order or subscription reference when available.
      </p>

      <h2>How Refunds Are Processed</h2>
      <p>
        Approved refunds are processed back to the original payment method
        through Creem. Payment processor timing may vary by payment method,
        bank, and country. A refunded license or subscription may be disabled.
      </p>

      <h2>Non-Refundable Cases</h2>
      <p>
        Refunds may be declined for abuse, fraud, chargebacks already filed,
        repeated refund requests, violations of the Terms of Service, or
        requests made after the refund window unless required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>Cancellation</h2>
      <p>
        You can cancel a subscription to stop future renewal. Cancellation does
        not automatically refund previous charges, but you may still request a
        refund under this policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Request A Refund</h2>
      <p>
        Send refund requests to
        <a href="mailto:support@rustzen.dev">support@rustzen.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
